cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.CC, cs.DS

This paper discusses the properties of a permutation function that can be used in symmetric cryptosystems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves the study of differential uniformity and nonlinear properties of the function, which falls under the category of cs.IT (Information Theory). The function is also related to control systems and dynamical systems, which could place it under cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper involves the study of permutations and mappings, which could fall under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
